[src:special-functions/error-function] In statistics, for non-negative real values of X , the error function has the following interpretation: for a real random variable Y that is normally distributed with mean 0 and standard deviation $1/{\sqrt {2}}$ , $\operatorname {erf} (x)$ is the probability that Y falls in the range $[-x,x]$ .
